    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Front and Side Cover</title>
        <figure id="f47006212" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g47006212.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 212. Steering Wheel Front Cover</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. FRONT COVER</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">The steering wheel removal process is intended for the removal of the component parts of
                the steering wheel assembly. Special note should be taken in the steering wheel mounted switches.
                Depending on municipality requirements the steering wheel switch options may vary.
            </emph>
        </para>
        <figure id="f47006213" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g47006213.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="288px"/>
            <caption>Figure 213. Releasing Front Cover With Tool</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To release front cover, insert removal tool (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f47006213">Figure 213</hotlnk>) into aperture. Phillips head screwdriver may be used.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Push inward to release steering wheel cover retaining clips.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f47006214" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g47006214.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 214. Removing Cover</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Grasp cover as shown (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f47006214">Figure 214</hotlnk>). Lift cover from steering wheel assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f47006215" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g47006215.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 215. Side Cover Removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. TURN SIGNAL SWITCH</callout1>
                <callout1>2. SIDE COVER</callout1>
                <callout1>3. RETAINING SCREW</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the steering column cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f47006215">Figure 215 Item 3</hotlnk>) fastener openings on the underside of steering
                wheel covers.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert Phillips head screwdriver in cover opening, loosen Phillips head screw and remove.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove side covers.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
